03/02/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatian Prime Minister Ivica Racan sent condolences to US President George W Bush and Israeli Prime Minister Ariel Sharon Sunday (2 February), following the space shuttle Columbia tragedy.
Racan said Croatians are mourning the tragedy as their own loss and as a loss for the whole of progressive society.
Also in Croatia, President Stipe Mesic appointed retired Gen Imra Agotic as his advisor on national security as of 1 February, relieving Zeljko Bagic.
Agotic was a presidential advisor on defence and security issues before the reshuffle.
(HINA - 03/02/03;
02/02/03)
